  <title>set_max_length</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(gint)
@returns(none)
def set_max_length(max_length)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Sets the maximum allowed length of the contents of the buffer. If
the current contents are longer than the given length, then they
will be truncated to fit.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>max_length :</p></td>
<td><p>the maximum length of the entry buffer, or 0 for no maximum. (other than the maximum length of entries.) The value passed in will be clamped to the range [ 0, %CLUTTER_TEXT_BUFFER_MAX_SIZE ].</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.10</p>
